comments: Lopez (CHI) establishes himself in a screening position in the path of Bembry (ATL) and is in a wide stance but no leg to leg contact occurs.
Carter (ATL) makes contact to the arm of Lopez (CHI) in the post and that contact affects his FOM.
Lopez (CHI) establishes himself in a screening position in the path of Bembry (ATL) when both players arms come together but they are able to disengage from the marginal contact.
Dedmon (ATL) cleanly blocks LaVine's (CHI) driving shot attempt.
Porter Jr. (CHI) reaches in and makes incidental contact with Young's (ATL) hand on the ball during his driving shot attempt.
LaVine (CHI) establishes himself in a screening position in the path of Carter (ATL) and does not deliver contact.
Carter (ATL) maintains a legal guarding position during the jump shot attempt by Porter Jr. (CHI).
Lopez (CHI) exits the paint within three seconds.
Porter Jr. (CHI) brings one hand to the opposite side of Carter's (ATL) body but he immediately removes it as Carter (ATL) moves away.
Markkanen (CHI) maintains a legal guarding position during the jump shot attempt by Prince (ATL).
Dunn (CHI) gives Young (ATL) room to land on the jump shot attempt.
Dedmon (ATL) makes contact with Porter Jr.'s (WAS) arm that affects his ability to follow through naturally on his jump shot attempt.

LLS shows Dedmon (ATL) is outside of the restricted area, but he is late to the spot and fails to establish himself in a legal guarding position at the time of the contact with LaVine (CHI) during his driving shot attempt.
Len (ATL) collapses his left arm to his body and absorbs the body contact from Markkanen (CHI) and cleanly blocks the driving shot attempt.
Porter Jr. (CHI) and Len (ATL) engage and disengage during the rebound.
Carter (ATL) reaches in and makes marginal contact with Porter Jr.'s (CHI) arm that does not affect his ability to get the rebound.
Carter (ATL) commits a take foul on Selden (CHI).
[Observable in enhanced video] Carter (ATL) stands with a foot on the lane line and is in the paint for longer than three seconds without actively guarding an opponent.
Len (ATL) cleanly blocks LaVine's (CHI) jump shot attempt and makes slight contact to LaVine's head after the blocked shot.
[Observable in enhanced video] Young (ATL) slides his pivot foot at the start of his dribble.
[Observable in enhanced video] Carter (ATL) slides his pivot foot at the start of his dribble.
Selden (CHI) makes incidental contact with Carter (ATL) after he has released his shot attempt that does not affect his ability to follow through naturally.
LaVine (CHI) extends his arm slightly but does not dislodge Bembry (ATL) from his defensive position.
Bembry (ATL) maintains legal guarding position and makes incidental contact with LaVine (CHI) that does not affect his SQBR.
Prince (ATL) and Porter Jr. (CHI) engage and disengage during rebounding.
LaVine (CHI) places his hand momentarily on Len's (ATL) hip and immediately corrects.
Markkanen (CHI) maintains legal guarding position and makes incidental contact with Young (ATL) that does not affect his SQBR.
Len (ATL) is in the lane and his shot attempt is imminent within three seconds.
RLS shows Selden (CHI) extends his arm into Len's (ATL) body and affects his shot near the rim.
Bembry (ATL) legally contests LaVine's (CHI) jump shot attempt.  Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Len (ATL) is already in LaVine's (CHI) path when contact occurs and he does not deliver contact.
Markkanen (CHI) makes marginal contact with Young (ATL) on the perimeter.
Len (ATL) is in the paint for longer than three seconds.
